Charge List
Miscellaneous Felony
Charge Fine Sentence Licences Definition
Accessory to Felony $3,500 600 days Anyone who attempts to help or aid someone in the preparation, act or escape of a felony offence.
Aircraft Hijacking $20,000 1200 days Unlawfully gaining control over an aircraft, forcing the manoeuvres of the pilot or operating the aircraft themselves.
Burglary $6,000 800 days Unlawfully entering into a dwelling or private premises with the clear intent to commit a criminal act while on said property.
Escaping Lawful Custody $10,000 1000 days Fleeing from the lawful custody of a law enforcement officer.
Felony Evading Arrest $4,000 800 days Impound Vehicle The act of intentionally fleeing from a law enforcement officer attempting to make a lawful arrest or detainment by means of giving verbal or visual directions, the announcement of their presence, or the operation of their emergency vehicle (such as lights, sirens, or a combination of both.)
Human Trafficking $10,000 1000 days The transportation, transfer, harbouring or receipt of a person(s) against their will in exchange for goods or money.
Illegal Gambling $20,000 1500 days Hosting or organising games/activities that involve a gambling or betting element with no valid Gambling Permit for said game/activity.
Impersonation of a Lawyer or Government Official $4,000 600 days The self portrayal of a lawyer or government official in an attempt to fool another or gain access to restricted areas. Or, the operation of a governmental-issued vehicle with the usage of emergency equipment.
Jailbreak $15,000 1500 days The act of attempting to or successfully freeing someone else from custody/prison.
Perjury $10,000 1000 days The act of willfully and deliberately providing false information while under oath.
Theft of Emergency vehicle $3,000 600 days The theft of an emergency vehicle. This includes Fire service, EMS, Law enforcement & Lifeguard.
Trespassing on Airport Property $5,000 800 days Unauthorized entering or remaining upon restricted government/private property that is utilized as an airport, airfield, runway, landing strip or helipad. This includes Los Santos International Airport, Sandy Shores Airfield, Grapeseed McKenzie Airfield and Cayo Perico Airstrip.
Trespassing with the Intent of Theft $2,500 500 days Entering or remaining upon restricted government/private property in which you can reasonably prove the intent of theft. This can include tools to aid in breaking entry. This is not stackable with Commercial Break In.
Witness Intimidation $10,000 1500 days The threatening of crucial court witnesses by pressure or extortion to compel them to not to testify.
Violent Crimes
Charge Fine Sentence Licences Definition
An act of Terrorism $25,000 1500 days Requires Judge Authorization The act of creating mass destruction via explosive destruction or mass shootings in highly populated areas to assert political or ideological control or fear into the public. - Requires Judge Authorization
Armed Robbery $6,000 800 days The act of depriving someone of or actively taking their property through the threat of violence in the presence of a weapon.
Arson $5,000 600 days The criminal act of intentionally setting fire to property.
Assault $2,000 300 days A threat of bodily harm coupled with an apparent, present ability to cause the harm.
Assault with a Firearm $7,000 900 days Revoke Weapons License The use of a firearm for the purpose of making violent threats against another person.
Attempted Mass Murder $20,000 2000 days Revoke Weapons License Taking substantial steps to end the life of three or more people, or taking action towards a group of three or more people deliberately or recklessly with extreme disregard for human life. Only stackable via multiple warrants.
Bank Robbery $10,000 1200 days The act of or direct involvement in stealing property from a bank, including removing property from the vault.
Battery $3,000 600 days An intentional unpermitted act causing harmful or offensive contact with another (includes hitting a person or spitting on them).
Commercial Break In $6,000 1000 days The act of or direct involvement in the planning of or acting upon breaking into either a commercial property or secured industrial container. (This does not extend to store robberies are they are covered in their own charge.)
Depository Robbery $40,000 3000 days The act of or direct involvement in stealing money or property from a state or federal depository.
High Felony Store Robbery $16,000 1600 days The act of or direct involvement in the theft of money or property from a high end store, i.e. a jewelry store, through the use of violence or force.
Kidnapping $5,000 900 days Revoke Weapons License The act of or direct involvement in the unlawful taking and movement of a person by force, fraud, or by means of a credible threat against their will, or the unlawful seizure and detainment of a person against their will by means of force or use of a credible threat.
Mass Jailbreak $40,000 3500 days Revoke Weapons License The act of attempting to or successfully freeing three or more people from custody/prison.
Murder $10,000 1200 days Revoke Weapons License Murder is the unlawful killing of a human being (not revived by EMS) with malice aforethought.
Preparing an act of Terrorism $20,000 1000 days Requires Judge Authorization A plot to commit an act of mass destruction or casualty for political gain. - Requires Judge Authorization
Store Robbery $6,000 700 days The act of or direct involvement in the theft of money or property from a store through the use of violence or force.
Vehicular Manslaughter $4,000 700 days Revoke Driving License Causing the unintentional death of a person or other driver through reckless, dangerous or negligent driving.

Poaching $1,800 200 days Revoke Hunting and Fishing License The illegal hunting, pursuing, trapping, harassing, catching, killing, taking, transporting, or possession any portion of any wildlife, except fish, without having first procured a license from the Department of Wildlife Conservation and/or Off the Bone. Alternatively, the hunting, pursuing, trapping, harassing, catching, killing, taking, transporting, or possessing any portion of any endangered or protected wildlife listed as follows: (1) Whales, (2) Dolphins, (3) Sharks, (4) Orcas, or (5) Stingrays.

Public Urination $100 0 days Dispersal Order Urinating in a public place like a park, alley, or sidewalk. It is considered a public nuisance.
Resisting Arrest $1,500 400 days The act of intentionally obstructing detainment into lawful custody.
Stalking $2,000 500 days The repeated following and harassing of another person with the intent to instill fear or injury.
Theft $2,500 800 days The act of depriving someone of money and/or items without prior consent from that individual.
Threat To Life $3,000 500 days To make a genuine and credible threat to kill another person.
Trespassing $2,000 200 days Entering or remaining upon restricted government/private property. This does not include public car parks.
Unlawful Discharge of a Firearm $2,000 400 days The reckless, negligent or unsafe use of a firearm in a public place.
Unlicensed Business $15,000 0 days Owning, operating, or directly aiding in the operation of a private business on private property OR public property without the appropriate certificates. This excludes public business such as, LTD, Bars, Ammu-Nations, etc.
Unlicensed Event $10,000 0 days Hosting or aiding in the hosting of an illegally planned event on private property OR public property without the appropriate permits.

Vehicular Related
Charge Fine Sentence Licences Definition
Breach of Airspace Regulations - Major $100,000 1000 days Requires Judge Authorization | Aviation Licence 2 minor infractions or 1 major infraction of the airspace regulations during the operation of an aircraft (https://tinyurl.com/HL-FS-Airspace-Regulations). Major infractions include but are not limited to: 100 to 300 feet below minimum altitude, major infraction on landing exceptions, intentionally obstructing another aircraft, landing within a class 2 airspace, unnecessary remaining within a class 2 airspace, intentionally risking property damage.
Breach of Airspace Regulations - Minor $50,000 0 days A single minor infraction of the airspace regulations while operating an aircraft (https://tinyurl.com/HL-FS-Airspace-Regulations). Minor infractions include but are not limited to: 0 to 100 feet below minimum altitude, minor infraction on landing exceptions, unintentional obstruction of another aircraft, speeding during taxiing, failure to be present in the Air Traffic radio, or any other infractions that do not bring a risk higher than low for life and medium for property.
Breach of Airspace Regulations - Severe $150,000 1600 days Requires Judge Authorization | Aviation License A single severe infraction or 2 or more major infractions of the airspace regulations while operating an aircraft (https://tinyurl.com/HL-FS-Airspace-Regulations). Severe infractions include but are not limited to: more than 300 feet below minimum altitude, landing in urban areas, entering prohibited airspace, intentional endangerment of life, using an aircraft for threats/acts of terrorism, use of an aircraft as a weapon or intimidation method.
Careless Driving $600 300 days Impound Vehicle - 3000 days Careless Driving shall be satisfied by a minimum of 2 separate traffic offences occurring simultaneously or within succession of each other.
Criminal Use of an Aircraft $25,000 1400 days Requires Judge Authorization | Aviation License The intentional use of an aircraft in the act of or aiding in a felony offense.
Driving Under the Influence (DUI) $1,000 400 days Revoke Driving License Operating a motor vehicle whilst over the prescribed limit of alcohol or drugs.
Driving without a License $400 300 days Impound of Vehicle Driving any street vehicle without a proper license.
Grand Theft Auto $1,000 300 days The operation of a motor vehicle without consent of the registered owner with the intent of permanently depriving them of the vehicle.
Hit and Run $3,000 700 days Revoke Driving License The act of hitting another vehicle or person whilst in control of a motor vehicle and failing to stop at the scene of the accident.
Reckless Driving $1,200 500 days Revoke Driving License | Impound Vehicle - 6000 Reckless Driving shall be satisfied by a minimum of 3 separate traffic offences occurring simultaneously or within succession of each other, or, a speeding offence of greater than 40 mph over the speed limit, or, mounting the sidewalk / leaving the roadway.
Taking Without Owner's Consent $750 150 days Taking a person's vehicle with the intention of returning the vehicle to them once used for its intended purpose. The perpetrator of this crime is often known to the victim i.e offspring, partner, sibling, friend etc.
Vehicular Battery $4,000 600 days Revoke Driving License An intentional unpermitted act of using a motor vehicle to cause harm or offensive contact with a person.
Corruption
Charge Fine Sentence Licences Definition
Bribery $4,000 400 days Persuading someone to commit an illegal act in exchange for a gift, money, service or other item.
Corruption $0 2000 days Removal From Position | Requires Judge Authorization | Fine TBD by judge A person in position of authority who wrongfully uses their place in office to benefit themselves or another person, contrary to duty and the rights of others. - Judges discretion
Embezzlement $6,000 800 days Fraudulent conversion of another's property by a person who is in a position of trust.
Extortion $4,000 700 days Unlawfully obtaining property that one is not entitled to at the time of threat, through the use of force or threats. In extortion the victim willingly hands over money, property or other valuables to avoid future violence or damages.
Fraud $0 1000 days Removal From Position | Requires Judge Authorization | Fine TBD by judge Wrongful or criminal deception intended to result in financial or personal gain and/or a person or thing intended to deceive others, typically by unjustifiably claiming or being credited with accomplishments or qualities.
Money Laundering $4,000 700 days Seizure of Offending Currency The process of taking the proceeds of criminal activity and making them appear legal.
Racketeering / RICO $0 0 days Requires Judge Authorization | Unlimited time and fine TBD by Judge Racketeer Influenced and Corrupt Organizations Clause (RICO) provides for extended criminal penalties for acts performed in support of an ongoing criminal organization. RICO allows leaders of the racket to be tried for ordering a crime without conducting it themselves.
Narcotics
Charge Fine Sentence Licences Definition
Class 1 Drug Manufacture and Supply $12,000 1000 days The ownership or aiding of a Class 1 drug growing operation on a small scale. This charge requires weed plants to be found and supporting evidence of the drug manufacturing process such as Class 1 drugs AND a plant pot, Miracle Gro, a watering can, or weed seeds. This stacks on every 4th plant. For example, 1 to 4 plants = 1 count, 5 to 8 plants = 2 counts, 9 to 12 plants = 3 counts, etc. 4 trimmings or 12 bags is equivalent to 1 plant.
Class 1 Drug Trafficking $8,000 800 days The possession OR aiding in the moving of weed, weed bags, weed trimmings, or boxes of weed of a quantity greater than 20 bags or a quantity equal to or greater than 1 box. This stacks every 60th bag. For example, 21 to 60 bags = 1 count, 61 to 120 bags = 2 counts, 121 to 180 bags = 3 counts, etc. 1 weed trimming is equivalent to 4 bags and 1 box of weed is equivalent to 60 bags.
Class 2 Drug Manufacture & Supply $20,000 1200 days Vehicle Impound The ownership or aiding in of a Class 2 production operation on a small scale. This charge requires the presence of Class 2 Drugs and supporting evidence of the drug manufacturing process such as a smoking RV, items required for the creation of the Class 2 drug, such as multiple chemicals, baking trays, bags or lab equipment for methamphetamine, or planters, Miracle Gro, watering cans, or shroom spores for shrooms. This stacks for every 3rd tray or planter. For example, 1 to 3 trays or planters = 1 count, 4 to 6 trays or planters = 2 counts, 7 to 9 trays or planters = 3 counts, etc. 2 packs or 8 bags of shrooms is equivalent to 1 planter, 20 bags of methamphetamine is equivalent to 1 block or tray, 1 slab of methamphetamine is equivalent to 3 blocks or trays, and 1 brick of methamphetamine is equivalent to 5 blocks or trays.
Class 2 Drug Trafficking $13,000 900 days The possession OR aiding in the moving of shrooms, shroom bags, shroom packs, boxes of shrooms, or methamphetamine of a quantity greater than 20 bags. This stacks for every 40 bags. For example, 21 to 60 bags = 1 count, 61 to 100 bags = 2 counts, 101 to 140 bags = 3 counts, etc. 1 box of shrooms is equivalent to 48 bags, 1 pack of shrooms is equivalent to 4 bags, 1 tray or block of methamphetamine is equivalent to 20 bags, 1 slab of methamphetamine is equivalent to 60 bags, and 1 brick of methamphetamine is equivalent to 100 bags.
Class 3 Drug Trafficking $20,000 1200 days The possession OR aiding in the moving of cocaine or heroin of a quantity greater than 20 bags or a quantity equal to or greater than 1 block, slab, brick, or tray, beginning on the 6th block. This stacks for every 3rd block. For example, 1 to 5 blocks = 1 count, 6 to 8 blocks = 2 counts, 9 to 11 blocks = 3 counts, etc. 20 bags is equivalent to 1 block, 1 slab is equivalent to 3 blocks, and 1 brick is equivalent to 5 blocks.
Distribution of Information $7,000 500 days The act or attempted act of selling information linked to the illegal pickup, processing or sale of prohibited items.
Importation Of Class 3 Drugs $25,000 1600 days The act of, aiding in, or attempted recovery of imported Class 3 substances. This charge requires the presence of cocaine, plus supporting evidence of the importation process, aiding of the importation process, or recovery of the imported contents i.e., individuals moving to and from any imported containers and their vehicles or identifying clothing linking individuals together.
Industrial Scale Drug Manufacture & Supply $50,000 2200 days Equipment Seized | Building is seized per Judge Authorization The ownership or co-ownership of a drug manufacturing facility of an industrial scale with the equipment for mass production.
Possession Of Class 1 Drug (Personal Use) $1,000 0 days The possession of weed, weed bags, or weed trimmings of a quantity between 1 to 10 bags. 1 weed trimming is equivalent to 4 bags.
Possession Of Class 1 Drug With Intent To Supply $4,000 500 days The possession of weed, weed bags, or weed trimmings of a quantity between 11 to 20 bags. Or, the possession of a Class 1 Drug and portable digital scales or resealable bags, regardless of quantity. This includes being in possession of less than the stated amount but evidence showing intent to supply. 1 weed trimming is equivalent to 4 bags.
Possession Of Class 2 Drug $4,000 300 days The possession of shrooms, packs of shrooms, shroom bags, or bags of methamphetamine of a quantity between 1 to 10 bags. 1 pack of shrooms is equivalent to 4 bags.
Possession Of Class 2 Drug With Intent To Supply $8,000 600 days The possession of shrooms, packs of shrooms, shroom bags, or methamphetamine of a quantity between 11 to 20 bags. Or, the possession of a Class 2 Drug and portable digital scales or resealable bags, regardless of quantity. This includes being in possession of less than the stated amount but evidence showing intent to supply. 1 pack of shrooms is equivalent to 4 bags.
Possession of Class 3 Drug With Intent to Supply $12,000 800 days The possession of cocaine or heroin of a quantity between 6 to 20 bags. Or, the possession of Class 3 Drugs and portable digital scales or resealable bags, regardless of quantity. This includes being in possession of less than the stated amount but evidence showing intent to supply.
Possession of Class 3 Drugs $6,000 600 days The possession of cocaine or heroin of a quantity of 5 bags or fewer.
Firearms/Explosives
Charge Fine Sentence Licences Definition
Distributing Legal Firearms to Unlicensed Owners $10,000 800 days Revoke Weapons License The act of distributing and/or selling a legal firearm to an unlicensed owner. This stacks every 3rd legal firearm provided to unlicensed owners. For example, 1 to 5 legal firearms = 1 count, 6 to 8 legal firearms = 2 counts, 9 to 11 legal firearms = 3 counts, etc.
Illegal Firearms Munitions Manufacture $80,000 3000 days Revoke Weapons License | Equipment Seized | Building is seized per Judge Authorization The ownership, aiding in, or use of an illegal weapons or ammunition manufacturing facility. This charge requires the presence of the manufacturing facility and the equipment for production. This charge stacks per manufacturing facility. Any illegal weapons, illegal weapon’s parts, or illegal weapon’s ammunition found in the facility would fall under their respective possession charges.
Illegal Weapons Trafficking $50,000 1800 days Revoke Weapons License The illegal sale of a firearm and/or the possession of three or more illegal firearms or production of prohibited firearms. Stacks every 3 illegal firearms. For example, 1 to 5 illegal firearms = 1 count, 6 to 8 illegal firearms = 2 counts, 9 to 11 illegal firearms = 3 counts, etc.
Possession of Explosives $10,000 800 days Revoke Weapons License Being in possession of explosive equipment or devices. This does not include the possession of fireworks.
Possession of Illegal Ammunition $3,000 300 days The possession of any illegal ammunition, i.e. SMG Ammunition, AK Ammunition. This stacks for every additional box of ammunition.
Possession of Illegal Weapon Parts $5,000 800 days Revoke Weapons License The possession of illegal weapons parts i.e. stocks, barrels, receivers, etc. Stacks for each individual illegal part they are in possession of.
Possession of Illegal Weapons Modification $3,000 600 days The possession of illegal weapons modifications such as a silencer, scope, or extended magazines. Stacks for each individual modification they are in possession of. This does not include modifications already attached to weapons or scopes on firearms by default such as a Hunting Rifle or the red dot sight on the M1911.
Possession of a Firearm Without a License $1,000 300 days Seizure of firearm Being in possession of a legal firearm but without the necessary license. Stacks every 3rd legal firearm without a license. For example, 1 to 5 legal firearms = 1 count, 6 to 8 legal firearms = 2 counts, 9 to 11 legal firearms = 3 counts, etc.
Possession of an Illegal Firearm Class 1 $7,000 700 days Revoke Weapons License The possession of any semi-automatic small arms firearm not purchasable via public gun store e.g. Glock, Tazer, Desert Eagle, Revolvers (except snubnose), double barrel shotgun.
Possession of an Illegal Firearm Class 2 $8,000 1000 days Revoke Weapons License The possession of any firearm capable of fully automatic discharge or rifle capable of semi automatic discharge. e.g. Assault rifles and submachine guns. This does not include the possession of a Hunting Rifle."
Possession of an Illegal Firearm Class 3 $10,000 1500 days Revoke Weapons License The possession of any long range precision rifle or modified class 1/2 firearm. i.e extended mag and/or barrel attachments.
Driving Infractions
Charge Fine Sentence Licences Definition
Driving Non-Street Legal Vehicle $300 0 days Impound Vehicle Operation of a Go-Kart, Monster Truck, Forklift, Baggage Cart, Lawn Mower, KX450F, or any vehicle with no plate on public roadways.
Excessive Vehicle Noise $100 0 days Honking of horns, blasting of music or the revving of engines which causes a public nuisance. Individuals should be given an opportunity to stop being fined.
Failure to Maintain a Lane $150 0 days Failing to stay within a legal lane of travel whilst driving and/or making an illegal turn based upon the lane turn arrows.
Failure to Stop $200 0 days Failure to come to a complete stop at a posted Stop sign or steady beam red light.
Failure to Yield to an Emergency Vehicle $320 0 days Failing to pull over, allow space or otherwise hinder an emergency vehicle in its response to an emergency.
Illegal Lighting Equipment $300 0 days Impound Vehicle Any aftermarket lighting will be considered illegal/unroadworthy if it is blue or red (including variations of light and dark). Impound may be considered for repeat offences where no attempt has been made to rectify the legality of the aftermarket lighting.
Illegal Parking $150 0 days Parking in a lane or on a sidewalk or any area deemed to be a hazard, including restricted zones. Proper parking is done by parking in between the white lines in a designated parking lot.
Illegal U-turn $150 0 days Making a 'U-turn' within city limits rather than doing a 'three point turn'.
Obstructing Traffic $400 0 days Intentionally causing/being an obstacle on a public road.
Speeding - Band 1 $200 0 days Operation of a Motor Vehicle 1mph - 10 mph over the speed limit.
Speeding - Band 2 $300 0 days Operation of a Motor Vehicle 11mph - 25 mph over the speed limit.
Speeding - Band 3 $400 0 days Impound Vehicle - 1500 days Operation of a Motor Vehicle 25 mph - 40 mph over the speed limit. After this it becomes reckless driving.
Using Mobile Phone Whilst Driving $200 0 days Operation of a motor vehicle whilst using a mobile phone.
